title: The Ultimate Worst-Case Scenario Survival Handbook (2012)
description:
The Ultimate Worst-Case Scenario Survival Handbook by David Borgenicht, Ben Winters
English | Sep. 19, 2012 | ISBN: 1452108285 | 272 Pages | EPUB | 17.9 MB

With over 9 million copies sold worldwide, the Worst-Case Scenario series has been preparing readers for dangers of all kinds for more than a decade. This compendium is truly the ultimate guide for handling life's inevitable Worst-Case Scenarios, collectingâ€”for the first timeâ€”hundreds of the best and most crucial scenarios from across the entire 26-book series, along with dozens of all-new and expanded scenarios, charts, and expert tips. Topical, tabloid-style pages explore more than 100 subjects, from storms to stampedes to technology failures and beyond, with special sections highlighting critical information on starting fires, animal encounters, emergency signals, "Can I eat that?" questions, and more. Packed with expert advice and sturdy enough to stop a tiger bite, this gifty tome will keep longtime fans and new initiates safe and entertained in equal measure
